Steps to creating/uploading the firmware

Dependencies (for Ubuntu/Debian):
- `make` (from `build-essentials`)
- `git` (for downloading the ardupilot source)
- `gcc-avr`

1. Download/compile customised APM firmware
  - `make`
2. Upload to the APM board
  - Select "Upload firmware" when connected via USB (but not connected in APM Planner)
3. Upload configuration
  - Select "Full parameter list", and "load from file", select `../WorkingConfig.param`
